# install.sh in symlink mode creates ~/.codex/skills/setup-codex-agenticapps-workflow/templates
# which resolves through the main symlink back into the source repo. The
# secondary symlink is regenerated by install.sh; tracking it would cause
# spurious diffs. v0.2.0 follow-up (Phase 6): restructure so install.sh in
# symlink mode does not need to write inside the source tree.
# Scoped to the setup skill only — other skills (e.g. codex-ts-declare-first)
# ship real, tracked template files under their own templates/ dir.
skills/setup-codex-agenticapps-workflow/templates
